title: XVIII: Heracles (Hercules) Can He Go the Distance? (Heracles Part Three)
itunes:title: XVIII: Heracles (Hercules) Can He Go the Distance? (Heracles Part Three)
itunes:subtitle: More of Heracles' labours, more comparisons to Disney.
description:
More of Heracles' labours, more comparisons to Disney, and a nifty use of a very large cup. Heracles has truly got it going on.


CW/TW: far too many Greek myths involve assault. Given it's fiction, and typically involves gods and/or monsters, I'm not as deferential as I would be were I referencing the real thing.


Sources: The Greek Myths by Robin Waterfield.


Attributions and licensing information for music used in the podcast can be found here: mythsbaby.com/sources-attributions.
